The paper deals with image denoising using deep learning, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new architecture for the denoising network, which involves convolutional and deconvolutional layers, and symmetric connections, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning also suggests a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with image processing, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
